Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of the K-means algorithm in multimedia and computer vision, which suggests that it is likely to be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel algorithm to reduce the computational complexity of the K-means algorithm, which suggests that it may also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of multiple random spatial partition trees, which suggests that it may be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the application of the proposed algorithm to image retrieval, which suggests that it may be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
